  {:unplunderable 1,
   :description
   ["While these were once considered cutting-edge outfits, their lack of autonomous capabilities and economic benefit ensured they were never licensed by a manufacturer."
    "\tDespite this, some captains commissioned these directly from their inventor, effectively replacing one of their crew members with a robotic counterpart. These captains found that androids possessed sufficient capabilities to perform most work, but lacked the capability to captain a ship or take part in boarding actions."],
   :category "Unique",
